{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,280p' apps/waketask-iphone/.github/workflows/ci.yml && sed -n '1,260p' apps/waketask-iphone/.github/workflows/ios-ci.yml\"","aggregated_output":"name: CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ main, develop ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ main, develop ]\n\n# Allow coverage comment step to post to PRs (read-only by default in newer repos).\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n  pull-requests: write\n\njobs:\n  test:\n    name: Build & Test (iOS 26.2)\n    runs-on: macos-15\n\n    steps:\n    - name: Checkout code\n      uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n    - name: Select Xcode 26.2\n      run: sudo xcode-select -s /Applications/Xcode_26.2.app/Contents/Developer\n\n    - name: Show Xcode version\n      run: xcodebuild -version\n\n    - name: Cache SPM dependencies\n      uses: actions/cache@v4\n      with:\n        path: |\n          ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/**/SourcePackages\n          .build\n        key: ${{ runner.os }}-spm-${{ hashFiles('**/Package.resolved') }}\n        restore-keys: |\n          ${{ runner.os }}-spm-\n\n    - name: Build for testing\n      run: |\n        xcodebuild \\\n          -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n          -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.2' \\\n          -derivedDataPath .build \\\n          build-for-testing\n\n    - name: Run tests with coverage\n      run: |\n        xcodebuild \\\n          -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n          -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.2' \\\n          -derivedDataPath .build \\\n          -enableCodeCoverage YES \\\n          test-without-building\n\n    # Coverage reporting is best-effort: Xcode 26's xccov output format\n    # changed vs the previous grep pattern and we'd rather ship the release\n    # than gate on a broken metric. Test failures still fail the job above.\n    - name: Generate coverage report\n      continue-on-error: true\n      run: |\n        xcrun xccov view --report .build/Logs/Test/*.xcresult > coverage.txt || true\n        cat coverage.txt || true\n\n    - name: Extract coverage percentage\n      id: coverage\n      continue-on-error: true\n      run: |\n        COVERAGE=$(xcrun xccov view --report .build/Logs/Test/*.xcresult | grep -E \"^\\s+SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.app\" | awk '{print $2}' | sed 's/%//' || echo \"\")\n        echo \"COVERAGE=${COVERAGE:-0}\" >> $GITHUB_OUTPUT\n        echo \"Coverage: ${COVERAGE:-unknown}%\"\n\n    - name: Upload coverage report\n      if: always()\n      continue-on-error: true\n      uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n      with:\n        name: coverage-report\n        path: coverage.txt\n\n    - name: Comment coverage on PR\n      if: github.event_name == 'pull_request'\n      continue-on-error: true\n      uses: actions/github-script@v7\n      with:\n        script: |\n          const fs = require('fs');\n          let coverage = '(coverage report unavailable)';\n          try {\n            coverage = fs.readFileSync('coverage.txt', 'utf8');\n          } catch {}\n          const coveragePercent = '${{ steps.coverage.outputs.COVERAGE }}' || 'n/a';\n\n          const body = `## 📊 Test Coverage Report\n\n          **Overall Coverage: ${coveragePercent}%**\n\n          <details>\n          <summary>Detailed Coverage</summary>\n\n          \\`\\`\\`\n          ${coverage}\n          \\`\\`\\`\n\n          </details>\n          `;\n\n          github.rest.issues.createComment({\n            issue_number: context.issue.number,\n            owner: context.repo.owner,\n            repo: context.repo.repo,\n            body: body\n          });\n\n  test-ios18-fallback:\n    name: Build & Test (iOS 18.6 fallback path)\n    runs-on: macos-15\n\n    steps:\n    - name: Checkout code\n      uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n    - name: Select Xcode 26.2\n      run: sudo xcode-select -s /Applications/Xcode_26.2.app/Contents/Developer\n\n    - name: Cache SPM dependencies\n      uses: actions/cache@v4\n      with:\n        path: |\n          ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/**/SourcePackages\n          .build-fallback\n        key: ${{ runner.os }}-spm-fallback-${{ hashFiles('**/Package.resolved') }}\n        restore-keys: |\n          ${{ runner.os }}-spm-fallback-\n\n    # Validates that SAIGlass's #available fallback to SwiftUI Material still\n    # compiles and runs on pre-iOS 26 simulators. No coverage gate — this job\n    # exists to catch regressions on the fallback path, not to block on metrics.\n    - name: Build for testing (iOS 18.6)\n      run: |\n        xcodebuild \\\n          -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n          -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 16 Pro,OS=18.6' \\\n          -derivedDataPath .build-fallback \\\n          build-for-testing\n\n    - name: Run tests (iOS 18.6)\n      run: |\n        xcodebuild \\\n          -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n          -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 16 Pro,OS=18.6' \\\n          -derivedDataPath .build-fallback \\\n          test-without-building\n\n  lint:\n    name: SwiftLint\n    runs-on: macos-15\n\n    steps:\n    - name: Checkout code\n      uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n    - name: Install SwiftLint\n      run: brew install swiftlint\n\n    - name: Run SwiftLint\n      run: swiftlint lint --strict\nname: iOS CI\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ main ]\n  pull_request:\n\njobs:\n  build-and-test:\n    runs-on: macos-15\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout\n        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Select Xcode 26.2\n        run: sudo xcode-select -s /Applications/Xcode_26.2.app || sudo xcode-select -s \"$(ls -d /Applications/Xcode_*.app | sort -V | tail -1)\"\n\n      - name: Cache SPM\n        uses: actions/cache@v4\n        with:\n          path: |\n            ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData\n            ~/Library/Caches/org.swift.swiftpm\n            ~/.swiftpm\n          key: ${{ runner.os }}-spm-${{ hashFiles('**/Package.resolved') }}\n\n      - name: Resolve packages\n        run: xcodebuild -resolvePackageDependencies -project SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj\n\n      - name: Build (Debug)\n        run: |\n          set -o pipefail\n          xcodebuild \\\n            -project SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj \\\n            -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n            -configuration Debug \\\n            -sdk iphonesimulator \\\n            -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.2' \\\n            CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO \\\n            build | xcpretty\n\n      - name: Test (Unit)\n        run: |\n          set -o pipefail\n          xcodebuild \\\n            -project SwiftAIBoilerplatePro.xcodeproj \\\n            -scheme SwiftAIBoilerplatePro \\\n            -sdk iphonesimulator \\\n            -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro,OS=26.2' \\\n            CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO \\\n            test | xcpretty --color\n\n      - name: Store logs\n        if: always()\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: xcode-logs\n          path: |\n            ~/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/**/Logs/Test/*\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"agent_message","text":"**Model Identity**\n`gpt-5-codex | Architecture Candidate: WakeTask-on-SwiftAIBoilerplatePro | Date: 2026-05-14`\n\n## 1) Keep Unchanged (reuse as-is)\n- `Packages/Core`, `Networking`, `Auth`, `Payments`, `AI`, `Localization`, `DesignSystem`.\n- `Storage` infrastructure primitives (SwiftData container, keychain/token plumbing, migration scaffolding).\n- Existing CI foundations in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and `ios-ci.yml` (macOS 15, Xcode 26.2, iOS 26.2 + iOS 18.6 fallback lane).\n- Existing Swift 6 conventions: `@MainActor` ViewModels, `any` existentials, `Sendable` protocol boundaries.\n\n## 2) Adapt (extend, don’t rebuild)\n- Add feature packages:\n  - `Packages/FeatureAlarm` (alarm setup/editing, strictness, scheduling orchestration).\n  - `Packages/FeatureWakeFlow` (active alarm UI, wake-check, escalation state machine).\n  - `Packages/FeatureMissions` (adaptive mission rotation across cognitive/movement/scan-photo).\n  - `Packages/FeatureReliability` (ledger/timeline + weekly consistency summary).\n  - `Packages/FeatureFirstTask` (post-wake micro-task bridge).\n- Extend `Packages/Storage` with WakeTask entities/repos:\n  - `Alarm`, `AlarmRun`, `WakeCheck`, `MissionAttempt`, `FirstTask`.\n  - Repos for ledger ordering, escalation outcomes, anti-repeat mission history.\n- Adapt AppShell navigation to add WakeTask tabs/flows while preserving existing launch/auth/paywall gates.\n- Keep ad SDKs out of critical wake path by architecture rule (no monetization hooks in alarm/wake modules).\n\n## 3) Remove (only if justified)\n- Remove/demo-disable generic chat-first surfaces from primary navigation **only if** they weaken 4.3 differentiation narrative.\n- Keep underlying AI package; do not remove infra. Use AI optionally for mission variation/personalization later.\n- Any removal must include ADR note: dependency impact + App Store 4.3 rationale.\n\n## 4) CompositionRoot Changes\n- Add new factories only in `CompositionRoot+Factories.swift`:\n  - `makeAlarmListViewModel()`, `makeAlarmEditorViewModel(alarmID:)`\n  - `makeWakeFlowViewModel(alarmID:)`\n  - `makeReliabilityLedgerViewModel()`\n- Register new repositories/services in `CompositionRoot.swift` with strict boundaries:\n  - `any AlarmRepository`, `any AlarmRunRepository`, `any MissionEngine`, `any WakeEscalationService`.\n- Keep constructor-driven DI, no feature-local singleton creation.\n\n## 5) DesignSystem Usage\n- Reuse token system (`DSColors`, `DSSpacing`, typography modifiers, `SAIGlass` wrappers).\n- Create WakeTask-specific components in feature modules but composed from DS primitives:\n  - `WakeCountdownCard`, `MissionStepCard`, `ReliabilityTimelineRow`.\n- Enforce accessibility defaults: Dynamic Type, VoiceOver labels, 44x44 targets, high-contrast countdown/action states.\n\n## 6) Data / Repository / Client Plan\n- Data layers:\n  - Local-first SwiftData for alarms, runs, mission attempts, first-task completion.\n  - Optional sync hooks can reuse existing Supabase patterns, but MVP logic remains on-device for privacy/NFR-05.\n- Repository boundaries:\n  - ViewModels only talk to protocols in feature/domain layer.\n  - Repositories own mapping, persistence, ordering, and failure reason normalization.\n- Client boundaries:\n  - Notification scheduling client adapter (UNUserNotificationCenter abstraction).\n  - Optional sensor/vision validators as protocol clients (scan/photo mission checks).\n\n## 7) ViewModel Boundaries\n- `AlarmEditorViewModel`: create/edit/validate alarm + strictness + mission stack.\n- `WakeFlowViewModel`: runtime state machine only (triggered → mission(s) → wake-check → escalation → first-task done).\n- `ReliabilityLedgerViewModel`: read-only timeline projection and weekly stats.\n- `FirstTaskViewModel`: completion gating for wake-flow terminal state.\n- Rule: no cross-feature mutable state except via repositories/services.\n\n## 8) Swift 6 Concurrency Risks\n- Risk: timer/escalation and notification callbacks crossing actors.\n  - Mitigation: isolate wake state machine in one actor (`WakeFlowEngine`) and bridge to `@MainActor` VM updates.\n- Risk: SwiftData context misuse off main actor.\n  - Mitigation: follow existing storage actor/MainActor patterns; explicit background context wrappers for heavy writes.\n- Risk: race between dismissal and wake-check timeout.\n  - Mitigation: idempotent transitions with monotonic run-state versioning.\n\n## 9) Test Plan (mapped to FR/NFR)\n- Unit:\n  - Mission rotation anti-repeat rules (`FR-02`).\n  - Wake escalation transitions and timeout handling (`FR-03`).\n- Integration:\n  - Repository writes/read order for reliability ledger (`FR-04`).\n  - CompositionRoot wiring for new factories/dependencies.\n- UI/XCTest:\n  - Create/edit alarm persistence (`FR-01`).\n  - Wake flow blocked until first-task complete (`FR-05`).\n- Non-functional:\n  - Launch p95 and interaction p95 metrics in CI artifacts (`NFR-01`,`NFR-02`).\n  - Accessibility assertions on critical wake screens (`NFR-04`).\n\n## 10) Appium Exploratory Harness Plan\n- Produce `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json` with required schema:\n  - `ok`, `buttons_tapped`, `screens_visited`, `crashes`, `failures`, `failures_detail`.\n- Breadth-first tap traversal across reachable MVP screens with backtracking.\n- Pass gate requires `buttons_tapped > 0`, `crashes=0`, `failures=0`.\n- Deferral only when both are present: `defer_appium: true` + documented simulator blocker.\n\n## 11) GitHub macOS CI Plan\n- Keep existing workflow topology and extend with a blocking `ios-quality` lane:\n  - `xcodebuild build` + `xcodebuild test` on iPhone 17 Pro / iOS 26.2.\n  - Fallback compile/test lane on iPhone 16 Pro / iOS 18.6.\n  - Blocking checks: SwiftLint, SwiftFormat, Qlty, secret scan, release-string audit (4.3 hardening), Swift file <=400 LOC guard.\n- Upload artifacts:\n  - `reports/ios/ios-quality-report.json`\n  - `reports/ios/appium-exploratory-report.json`\n  - test/coverage logs.\n- Release blocked unless DoD-04..DoD-18 evidence is present."}}
