d **copy-paste email** text for your delivery workflow.\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:110:- **Xcode pin** — all three workflows (`ci.yml`, `ios-ci.yml`, `coverage-report.yml`) select `Xcode_26.2`.\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:113:- **Dropped `package-tests` matrix** — its `cd Packages/X && swift test` invocations targeted the host macOS and could not compile iOS-only SwiftUI. Package code is still exercised by the app test suite (115 tests).\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:126:- **Secrets workflow** — `.githooks/pre-commit` blocks commits of non-placeholder values in `Generated/Configuration.swift`; `scripts/update-config.sh` warns not to commit after injecting real keys (install hook with `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`).\napps/waketask-iphone/RELEASE_NOTES.md:160:- ✅ **115 tests, 0 failures** on iPhone 17 Pro / iOS 26.2 (`xcodebuild test`)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:36:- **macOS 15+ with Xcode 26.2+** — v2.0 uses the iOS 26 SDK to compile Liquid Glass APIs (`Glass`, `glassEffect`, `GlassEffectContainer`). Runtime still supports iOS 17+ via a SwiftUI `Material` fallback.\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:40:- [SwiftLint](https://github.com/realm/SwiftLint) — `brew install swiftlint` (optional, matches the CI lint job)\napps/waketask-iphone/README.md:471:xcodebuild test \\\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/Tests/StorageTests/MigrationTests.swift:5:@available(iOS 17.0, macOS 14.0, *)\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/Tests/StorageTests/MemoryRetrieverTests.swift:6:@available(iOS 17.0, macOS 14.0, *)\napps/waketask-iphone/Packages/Storage/Tests/StorageTests/MemoryRepositoryTests.swift:6:@available(iOS 17.0, macOS 14.0, *)\napps/waketask-iphone/SKILLS.md:30:| **iOS Simulator** | `conorluddy/ios-simulator-skill` | 21 scripts for simulator automation with semantic navigation. 96% token reduction vs raw tools. Build, test, analyze without leaving the terminal | Automated testing, CI/CD, build workflows |\napps/waketask-iphone/S